                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                <date>20 Oct 54</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I have been quite unable to answer<lb/> your favor of <date>12<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> inst until now, having had so<lb/> many calls upon\n                my leisure—not the least pleasant<lb/> of which was the arrival here of my brother from<lb/>\n                <placeName>London</placeName>.Your reply with reference to the publishing<lb/> of\n                school books is certainly satisfactory so far as<lb/> your willingness to unite with\n                me in the undertaking<lb/> is concerned, but permit me to say it is less so\n                with<lb/> reference to other points. You say when you have<lb/> returned from your\n                collecting tour you will be able<lb/> to speak more positively as to what can be\n                done in<lb/> the matter of printing school books; Am I to<lb/> understand that your\n                willingness to go on<lb/> depends upon your success in collecting? Please<lb/>\n                recollect in the matter of <persName>Templo's</persName> Grammar that<lb/> it is not\n                pleasant for me to appear laboring so<lb/> many months in advertisement to produce a<lb/>\n                <persName><hi rend=\"underline\">Leão</hi> (Templo)</persName> and yet not even\n                producing a mouse<lb/> nor, perhaps, would it be quite right to withdraw<lb/> my\n                advt unless I announced there would certainly<lb/> appear jointly that book or one similar—whether<lb/>\n                <persName>Leesers</persName> or <persName>Templo's</persName> would not much matter\n                so<lb/> that we had the one best adapted for schools<lb/> that at least one person\n                expects the book Templo</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vd6pr09/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
