                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>and has paid for it the enclosed will testify.<lb/> Please return me <persName>Mr\n                    Alexander's</persName> letter in your<lb/> next favor. Do you know him?</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I would beg to ask you one question, do<lb/> you object to increase\n                “the burthen under which<lb/> you stagger” by “going halves” as the school boys<lb/>\n                say in producing <hi rend=\"underline\">only</hi>\n                <persName>Templos</persName> book or a<lb/> Hebrew Grammar. Without involving either\n                of us<lb/> to any large amount we show that we are in the full with <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">the right article</hi> and we shall<lb/> have made a\n                commencement. I do not say we should<lb/> print before you return “about\n                    <date>Purim</date> time”<lb/> but I do think that before you commence your<lb/>\n                trip I would find it very acceptable were the<lb/> public notified of a contemplated\n                joint publica<lb/> of a Heb. Gram. as a positive thing; and as a thing<lb/> not so\n                positive, but dependent upon the support<lb/> they extend to the plan—inform them of\n                the<lb/> projected issue of the other books named. A<lb/> comprehensive good Hebrew\n                Grammar is unquestionably<lb/> wanted—we have\n                    <persName>Nerurtz's<add>?</add></persName> but it is too<lb/> large and\n                expensive, <persName>Newmans</persName> is too <sic>meagre</sic><lb/> and too badly\n                arranged, all others in the English<lb/> language by Jews or Christians for\n                Jewish<lb/> schools are in my estimation worth <hi rend=\"underline\">nichts</hi><lb/>\n                I have no fear that any of the books I before<lb/> referred to will not make their\n                way &amp; expenses<lb/> support before hand I do not like to solicit. I<lb/> would\n                therefore much like to hear that you</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vd6pr09/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
