                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vd6pr09/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>are disposed to make announcement in your next<lb/> Occ. that out we will come\n                    <del>and</del> that I may be<lb/> enabled to withdraw my advertisement from\n                the<lb/> Asmonean &amp; supply #c notification of <persName>Templo's</persName>\n                appear-<lb/>ance under altered circumstances. You say you<lb/> do not know the\n                books. I could send it you on by express<lb/> to look at. It requires a little\n                alteration of arrangement<lb/> and will make about <hi rend=\"underline\">70\n                    pages</hi>\n                <add>?</add>. I think it<lb/> a good book so do many others, my brother among\n                them<lb/>—but I would of course like your opinion.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am sorry you were not here <add>Hebrew</add>. I should be<lb/>\n                much pleased if next year, <persName>D. L.</persName> you extend your<lb/> visit and\n                come to us. I should be very glad to hear<lb/> you read what portion of the prayers\n                you prefer<lb/> while in exchange I could myself stand <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> as\n                said the <add>?</add> lingue of our friend. What I can<lb/> do for your Bibles\n                defence I will. I don't know<lb/> why the Oc. comes late, but it comes late.\n                    <persName>Mrs<lb/> S<add>?</add> Joseph</persName> is sullen<add>?</add> and I\n                believe proposes taking<lb/> a trip south. The prayer books being too late<lb/> I\n                can be explained by the party's altering his mind<lb/> that a set cost “viel geld”\n                and a secondhand one<lb/> could be got cheaper—hence the excuse “too late<lb/> when\n                    <add>Hebrew</add> was only a week off and no books<lb/> had arrived. It is not\n                the first time <add>?</add> have<lb/> changed their minds after ordering my\n                fathers'.<lb/> I must close though I have more to write<lb/> Hoping to hear soon\n                from you I am</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Yours truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Abraham de Sola</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>will you please have the</p>\n            <p>enclosed to <persName>Miss Gratz</persName>?</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vd6pr09/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
